 and fixes Review complex problem situations and identify preventive measures / improvements to processes, procedures or tools, and implement these as required Maintain up-to-date knowledge of all operational security and emergency procedures Participate in SAP Basis component upgrades and migration projects Install and maintain servers, operating systems, and network equipment Ongoing internal training sessions specific to SAP technologies and oXya services delivery procedures Required Skills & Experience: Proven experience with SAP Basis administration Some exposure to Installation, Upgrades, OS/DB migrations preferred Self-motivated and resourceful Proactive as it relates to improvements and administration of SAP Landscapes Good interpersonal skills for interacting with team members and customers cross functionally and cross geographically Valid passport, international travel may be required Passionate and positive attitude essential Ability to work in teams Fluency in English All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, place of origin, ethnic origin, national origin, ancestry, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, transgender status, genetic information, mental or physical disability, marital status, pregnancy, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable national, state, or local law. Job Type: Full-time Experience: Information Technology: 3 years (Required) Work authorization: United States (Required) Application Question: Will you now, or in the future, require sponsorship for employment visa status (e.g. H-1B visa status)?\" "
